witter.com/carlquintanilla/status/1765908327639179307">能源独立</a>。但更重要的是太阳能和电池成本的<a href="https://twitter.com/threekardashevs/status/1766264117634195895">大幅下降</a>。近一个世纪以来，我们第一次发现新能源技术比旧能源技术效果更好。因此，世界正在加速安装大量太阳能和电池也就不足为奇了。当然，中国是这方面的领头羊，但美国也<a href="https://www.nathanielbullard.com/presentations">进行了大量投资</a>——建设太阳能工厂、购买电动汽车和建设电池工厂。</p><p><a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/repost-why-im-so-excited-about-solar">我对此感到兴奋的</a>原因——以及为什么你也应该感到兴奋——是<em>生产力</em>。就在 20 世纪 70 年代初美国生产率增长放缓之际，石油危机导致我们<a href="https://worksinprogress.co/issue/making-energy-too-cheap-to-meter/">开始减少能源使用</a>： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F41ce0056-f84f-466e-bed3-f68a32a0dc97_915x528.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F41ce0056-f84f-466e-bed3-f68a32a0dc97_915x528.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F41ce0056-f84f-466e-bed3-f68a32a0dc97_915x528.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F41ce0056-f84f-466e-bed3-f68a32a0dc97_915x528.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F41ce0056-f84f-466e-bed3-f68a32a0dc97_915x528.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F41ce0056-f84f-466e-bed3-f68a32a0dc97_915x528.jpeg" width="915" height="528" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/41ce0056-f84f-466e-bed3-f68a32a0dc97_915x528.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:528,&quot;width&quot;:915,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:70746,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F41ce0056-f84f-466e-bed3-f68a32a0dc97_915x528.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F41ce0056-f84f-466e-bed3-f68a32a0dc97_915x528.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F41ce0056-f84f-466e-bed3-f68a32a0dc97_915x528.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F41ce0056-f84f-466e-bed3-f68a32a0dc97_915x528.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">资料来源：<a href="https://worksinprogress.co/issue/making-energy-too-cheap-to-meter/">本·莱因哈特</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>相关性不是因果关系，但有充分的理由认为物理（“原子”）技术比数字（“位”）技术更有利于复合生产力的提高。即使是人工智能也必须构建大量真实的物理东西才能实现其作为 GDP 加速器的承诺。显然，还有很多其他因素影响实物产品生产——邻避主义、环境监管、贸易模式等等——但能源供应可能是一个关键投入。凭借来自太阳能和电池的超廉价和超便携式能源，谁知道我们能实现什么——廉价的海水淡化、无处不在的廉价自动驾驶汽车和电动自行车、个人航空运输、超级动力<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/battery-powered-appliances">电器</a>、无处不在的机器人等等在。</p><p>但这个乌托邦正面临需求增长和供应有限的威胁。在需求方面，我们发明了可能会消耗任意大量电力的新数字技术：比特币和人工智能。而在供应方面，有一堆糟糕的政策导致新电源难以接入美国电网。</p><h4>为什么电力需求再次上升</h4><p>长期以来，美国电力需求基本持平。这导致人们对太阳能和其他可再生能源取代现有化石燃料技术的速度做出了很多乐观的预测。但与大流行以来的许多其他经济数据一样，我们发现经济的一个长期存在的结构性部分突然发生了变化。 <a href="https://www.canarymedia.com/articles/transmission/suddenly-us-electricity-demand-is-spiking-can-the-grid-keep-up">电力需求再次增长</a>：</p><blockquote><p>过去二十年来，美国各地的电力需求几乎没有增加。但这些动态似乎已经发生了戏剧性的逆转——美国电力公司、监管机构和电网规划者还没有准备好应对这种电力需求激增的新模式。</p><p>这是咨询公司 Grid Strategies 发布的一份名为<a href="https://gridstrategiesllc.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/National-Load-Growth-Report-2023.pdf">《电力需求扁平时代已经结束》</a>的新报告的主要结论……在过去的一年里，美国公用事业公司和电网运​​营商对未来五年电力需求增长量的估计几乎翻了一番，从 2.6% 跃升至 4.7%……这远远高于过去十年 0.5% 的年需求增长预期。 </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F12fad0d0-e9f9-4e7e-98c7-39d0cde528f7_817x758.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F12fad0d0-e9f9-4e7e-98c7-39d0cde528f7_817x758.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com