62845593494331824">的日本单间公寓的视频</a>： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5b6fc6fc-012f-4290-b221-6c080d38cd8b_919x816.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5b6fc6fc-012f-4290-b221-6c080d38cd8b_919x816.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5b6fc6fc-012f-4290-b221-6c080d38cd8b_919x816.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5b6fc6fc-012f-4290-b221-6c080d38cd8b_919x816.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5b6fc6fc-012f-4290-b221-6c080d38cd8b_919x816.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5b6fc6fc-012f-4290-b221-6c080d38cd8b_919x816.jpeg" width="588" height="522.0979325353645" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/5b6fc6fc-012f-4290-b221-6c080d38cd8b_919x816.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:816,&quot;width&quot;:919,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:588,&quot;bytes&quot;:96233,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5b6fc6fc-012f-4290-b221-6c080d38cd8b_919x816.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5b6fc6fc-012f-4290-b221-6c080d38cd8b_919x816.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5b6fc6fc-012f-4290-b221-6c080d38cd8b_919x816.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5b6fc6fc-012f-4290-b221-6c080d38cd8b_919x816.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></figure></div><p>现在，与美国顶级城市相比，这是一个<em>非常</em>好的价格。 250 平方英尺 300 美元，每平方英尺只需 1.2 美元！<a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2023/05/11/realestate/square-footage-rent-economy.html">去年的一项研究</a>发现，纽约市的租金比这个数字高得多——曼哈顿每平方英尺 6.17 美元，布鲁克林每平方英尺 4.39 美元，皇后区每平方英尺 3.82 美元。你必须一路前往堪萨斯州威奇托——调查中最便宜的城市——才能享受到与东京类似的价格。</p><p>当然，原因之一是东京等日本城市<a href="https://jamesjgleeson.wordpress.com/2018/02/19/how-tokyo-built-its-way-to-abundant-housing/">建造了大量住房</a>。但另一个原因是需求下降——平均而言，日本人<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disposable_household_and_per_capita_income#Median_equivalised_disposable_income">比美国人贫穷得多</a>，其可支配个人收入中位数的一半还不到。这意味着他们无力支付那么多的公寓费用，因此价格较低。</p><p>但这些价格是按单位建筑面积计算的。事实是，即使您为 250 平方英尺的公寓支付非常低的租金，您仍然住在一个非常小的公寓里。这还不是最小的——日本公寓也有小至 108 平方英尺的！</p><p>事实上，这与日本的常态相去甚远。微型公寓<a href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/archive/politics/1982/03/14/cramped-life-in-rabbit-hutches/35e7dda3-e257-4933-b751-42ae83a8f8ca/">曾经在东京很常见</a>，但这座城市大规模且持续的建筑热潮在 1968 年至 2013 年间使<a href="https://twitter.com/geographyjim/status/879027339505610753">人均建筑面积翻了一番</a>。这座城市现在的居住空间可与巴黎和伦敦相媲美，仅比纽约市稍小一些： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcb9e8d4c-573a-45e7-ae6a-626dc92e2070_1012x624.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcb9e8d4c-573a-45e7-ae6a-626dc92e2070_1012x624.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcb9e8d4c-573a-45e7-ae6a-626dc92e2070_1012x624.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcb9e8d4c-573a-45e7-ae6a-626dc92e2070_1012x624.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcb9e8d4c-573a-45e7-ae6a-626dc92e2070_1012x624.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcb9e8d4c-573a-45e7-ae6a-626dc92e2070_1012x624.jpeg" width="1012" height="624" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/cb9e8d4c-573a-45e7-ae6a-626dc92e2070_1012x624.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:624,&quot;width&quot;:1012,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:53692,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcb9e8d4c-573a-45e7-ae6a-626dc92e2070_1012x624.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcb9e8d4c-573a-45e7-ae6a-626dc92e2070_1012x624.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcb9e8d4c-573a-45e7-ae6a-626dc92e2070_1012x624.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcb9e8d4c-573a-45e7-ae6a-626dc92e2070_1012x624.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">资料来源： <a href="https://s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/airdrive-images/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/20200804092413/GLA-Housing-Research-Note-3-Housing-in-four-world-cities.pdf">格里森 (2019)</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>而其他日本城市<a href="https://resources.realestate.co.jp/living/how-much-living-space-does-the-average-household-have-in-japan/">则拥有更多的空间</a>。</p><p>但无论如何，其中一些小公寓仍然存在，所以让我们来谈谈它们。事实上，我25岁时，在一套比视频中的稍小的日本公寓里住了大约半年。是的，它很拥挤，但这实际上是一次非常好的居住体验。理解<em>为什么</em>这是一次美好的生活体验有助于理解为什么美国城市如此令人不满意。</p><p>许多美国人对生活在如此狭小的空间里感到震惊和恐惧。对于在郊区巨型房屋中长大的人们来说，大城市中的一间小公寓可能听起来像是反乌托邦——俗话说的“ <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20191021133957/http://dvspress.com/live-in-the-pod-and-eat-bugs/">生活在豆荚里</a>”。这种发自内心的恐惧不仅在保守派中，而且在一些左派和自由派中也引起了人们的担忧，担心<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/the-long-march-of-the-yimbys">YIMBY 政策</a>试图<em>迫使</em>美国人像沙丁鱼一样挤在一起生活在像上面视频中那样的小单位里。</p><p>这些恐惧是不合理的。 YIMBY 人不想强迫任何人住在狭小的公寓里；他们只是想允许建造这样的公寓，如果有人确实想住在里面的话。我就是其中之一。</p><p>为什么住在一个小公寓里这么好？当然，部分原因是我已经 25 岁了，生活自由自在，住在一个外国城市，经常参加派对。部分原因是，从文化上来说，日本是一个非常友好的地方（至少，如果你懂得说这种语言的话）。但这很大程度上与<em>日本城市的建设方式</em>有关。日本真正掌握了密集、多功能的城市化艺术。这意味着即使你住在一个小公寓里，你周围的城市却如此美好，让你的生活感觉非常自由和奢华。</p><h4>商业密度高的混合用途分区</h4><p><a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/why-japanese-cities-are-such-nice">阅读更多</a></p>;
